🎯 CSS to make the OK button normal size
Add this to your site stylesheet (site.css) or inside a <style> block:

css
/* Fix stretched OK button in kendo.alert() */
.k-dialog .k-dialog-buttongroup .k-button {
    width: auto !important;
    min-width: 90px; /* optional: keeps button looking standard */
    flex: 0 0 auto !important;
}
If your project uses the newer Bootstrap/Material Kendo themes, this variant ensures compatibility:

css
.k-window .k-dialog-buttongroup .k-button,
.k-dialog .k-dialog-buttongroup .k-button {
    width: auto !important;
    flex: 0 0 auto !important;
}
